Amazing sculptures but could use better maintenance
Feb 2017 • Family
The sculptures are simply amazing with Hindu and Buddhist influences. Some of the pieces have such vivid facial expressions and beautiful figures, they almost put tears to my eyes. The audio tour is pretty good, and makes up for the poor organization of the sculptures. The place is a little run-down, with dirty floors and watermarks on the walls. I hope the government tries to preserve their treasure a little more. And I hope the sculptures could be more well-organized, with the audio tour giving more background information. But it is a must-see in Danang.
